The paper uses graph theory to model the problem of selecting optimal programme slots in television channels, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and decision-making, which could fall under the categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the problem being addressed is a real-world problem, which could make it relevant to the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
